==Spanish==
===Etymology===
From a romance variation of the Latin ''[[ambulare|ambulāre]]''

===Verb===
'''andar'''

# to [[walk]], to [[go]]
# to [[amble]], to [[travel]]
# to [[function]], to [[work]], to [[go]]
# to [[pass]], to go by, to [[elapse]]
# to [[be]], to [[feel]]
#:¿Cómo andas? &mdash; ''How do you feel?''

# to be in a boyfriend/girlfriend relationship with someone (EG: "¿Quieres andar conmigo?" ("Do you want to be my boyfriend/girlfriend?); or "Juan anda con María," "Juan and Maria are dating").

